page.title: 19CURRIE SCHOOL CAMP
page.content: SCHOOL CAMP AT KINDROGAN FIELD CENTRE WAS ACTION PACKED AND VERY TIRING. WE GOT UP AT QUARTER PAST SEVEN AND GOT DRESSED. AFTER BREAKFAST WE MADE OUR PACKED LUNCH AND WENT TO THE CLASSROOM. WE COLLECTED NETS, TRAYS, JARS AND A PIPETTE. WE COLLECTED POND ANIMALS AND TOOK THEM BACK TO THE CLASSROOM TO IDENTIFY THEM. WE THEN PUT THEM IN SMALL CONTAINERS, PUT A PIECE OF PAPER BESIDE THEM AND WROTE THEIR NAMES ON THEM. AFTER THIS WE WENT TO THE RIVER AND DID EXACTLY THE SAME.WE WORKED ON THIS TILL SEVEN PM. THEN IT WAS TIME FOR DINNER.AFTER DINNER WE WENT DEER WATCHING AND SAW THIRTEEN DEER. AFTER DEER WATCHING IT WAS TIME FOR BED. WE THOUGHT KINDROGAN WAS WONDERFUL AND WE WOULD GO AGAIN IF WE HAD THE CHANCE.
